\0 does not stop the loop on line 13 because the result of ISSPACE() is false.
`
while(!ISSPACE(*tok_end))
`
If the result of ISSPACE() is false, while(!ISSPACE()) will be true.
There is a process to stop the loop when \0 on the 16th line, but before that there is a problem.
Also, even if you read outside the area and ISSPACE() returns true, the loop will continue if \0 is not after 1 byte.

When I ran it with the same arguments, it would sometimes succeed (and sometimes crash the application if I ran it multiple times).
I thought that the success/failure was related to the Uninitialized Stack Variables, but I'm still guessing.
